            "questionText": "A car battery with an electromotive force (EMF) of $!$\\varepsilon = 12\\,\\text{V}$!$ powers the headlights. When the headlights are turned on, a current of $!$I = 5\\,\\text{A}$!$ flows through them. The battery has an internal resistance of $!$r = 0.2\\,\\Omega$!$. The headlights are connected directly to the battery terminals. Calculate the power dissipated by the headlights, taking into account the effect of the battery's internal resistance on the terminal potential difference.",
            "imageText": "",
            "steps": [
                {
                    "id": "3eecc85e2e7a41d9add88",
                    "stepText": "Let's start by determining the voltage drop across the battery's internal resistance. Please choose the correct formula that relates the voltage drop to the current and resistance.",
